{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Maroc Hebdo | logo = | logo_size = | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file: prefix --> | image_size = <!-- (defaults to user thumbnail size if no size is stated) --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = Political magazine | frequency = Weekly | format = | circulation = 6,265 (2013) | publisher = | founder = [[Mohammed Selhami]] | founded ={{Start date and age|1991}} | firstdate = | company = | country = [[Morocco]] | based = [[Casablanca]] | language = [[French language|French]] | website = {{URL|www.maroc-hebdo.press.ma}} | issn = 1274-1167 | oclc = 74442678 }} '''''Maroc Hebdo''''' is a French-language weekly political [[magazine]] issued in [[Morocco]].
==History== ''Maroc Hebdo'' was established in 1991<ref>{{cite news|title=Le magazine Maroc Hebdo retiré des kiosques pour une carte du Maroc sans le Sahara|url=http://www.bladi.net/magazine-maroc-hebdo-carte-sahara,46976.html|accessdate=20 February 2017|work=Bladi|date=29 December 2016|language=French}}</ref> by [[Mohammed Selhami]] in [[Casablanca]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Maroc Hebdo|url=http://www.courrierinternational.com/notule-source/maroc-hebdo|accessdate=20 February 2017|work=Courrier International|language=French}}</ref> Mohammed Selhami also edited it.<ref>{{cite book|author=John Pierre Entelis|title=Islam, Democracy, and the State in North Africa|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5ev4ZSeKCw4C&pg=PA55|accessdate=11 May 2015|year=1997|publisher=Indiana University Press|isbn=0-253-21131-X|page=55}}</ref> In January 2005, it changed to the magazine format.<ref>{{cite news|title=Maroc Hebdo passe au magazine|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/lagazette/5647|accessdate=8 June 2014|work=[[La Gazette du Maroc]]|date=17 January 2005}}</ref>
The editorial stance of ''Maroc Hebdo'' is pro-government. In 2013 the magazine sold 6,265 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Maroc Hebdo International &ndash; Presse payante |url=http://www.ojd.ma/Adherents/Presse-payante/MAROC-HEBDO-INTERNATIONAL|work=OJD|accessdate=7 June 2014}}</ref>
==Homophobic controversy== On 12 June 2015, it published an issue with a [[homophobia|homophobic]] cover saying, "Shall we burn homosexuals?".<ref name="ibtumberto">Umberto Bacchi, [http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/morocco-anger-maroc-hebdo-magazine-cover-asking-shall-we-burn-homosexuals-1505818 Morocco: Anger at Maroc Hebdo magazine cover asking 'shall we burn homosexuals?'], ''International Business Times'', 12 June 2015</ref> Due to ensuing global outrage at the incitement of hatred, all copies were recalled.<ref name="yahooafp">[https://news.yahoo.com/moroccan-magazine-recalls-burn-gays-issue-uproar-200733030.html Moroccan magazine recalls 'burn gays' issue after uproar], ''Yahoo! News'', Agence France Presse, 12 June 2015</ref>
