'''Relief''', as a military term, refers to the breaking of a [[siege]] or an [[encirclement]] by an outside force.<ref>{{cite web|title=relief|url=http://www.thefreedictionary.com/relief|website=thefreedictionary.com|accessdate=24 April 2015}}</ref> Relief may occur in conjunction with a [[Breakout (military)|breakout]]. It is one of four possible [[result|conclusion]]s of [[Investment (military)|investment]], the others being a [[Breakout (military)|breakout]], [[surrender (military)|surrender]] or [[Reduction (military)|reduction]]. The force that effects relief is known as the "relieving force". Following relief, the town or fortification is said to have been "relieved".
== See also == * [[Relief in place]]
